Whoopie Pies

- 14 Tbsp butter
Allow butter to come to room temperature before starting

Put rack in lower third of oven and preheat to 375F.

- 283 g all-purpose flour
- 45 g dutched cocoa powder
- 1 tsp baking soda
- 1/2 tsp salt
Whisk dry ingredients in a large bowl until uniform.

- 200 g light brown sugar
- 1/2 cup buttermilk
- 1/2 cup vegetable oil
- 1 egg
- 1.5 tsp vanilla extract
Put brown sugar into a stand mixer, and break up any clumps.
Add buttermilk, oil, egg, and vanilla.
Mix using the paddle attachment until well-blended.

Add dry mix to wet mix.
Carefully use the paddle to mix just until evenly combined (do not over-mix).

- 1/2 cup hot tap water
Add to batter, then mix just until evenly combined.

Line a baking sheet with parchment.
Use medium cookie scoop to portion out first batch of cakes, leaving 2 inches in between.
The baking sheet will hold appx 9 cakes.

Bake for 10-15 minutes until a toothpick comes out clean.
Allow to cool on baking sheet for 5 minutes, then moves cakes to wire rack to fully cool.
Repeat with second batch of cakes.

Wash out stand mixer bowl and paddle. Dry thoroughly

- 270 g powdered sugar
- 1/3 tsp salt
Add butter, powdered sugar, and salt to stand mixer bowl.
Mix with paddle on low speed just until combined.
Increase to high speed and cream until light and fluffy, scraping down bowl a couple of times.

- 1 tsp vanilla extract
Add vanilla and beat until combined.

- 10 oz Fluff (more than a small jar!)
Add Fluff to butter mixture and fold by hand with a rubber spatula just until uniform.

When cakes are fully cool, match them up into pairs with cakes that are the same size/shape.
Attach a large circluar tip to a piping bag, and fill the bag halfway with cream filling.
For each pair of cakes, pipe a generous covering onto the flat side of one cake, then cover with the other cake.
Repeat for all pairs, refilling piping bag as necessary.

Wrap each cake individually with plastic wrap, and store at room temperature.
